            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>This copy from an edition of the<lb/> book in the <persName>Leeser</persName> Library
                was<lb/> commenced by <persName>Abraham Sulzberger</persName><lb/> on <date>October
                        12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1886</date>, he being then<lb/> very ill, feeble
                and despondent,<lb/> but from time to time he wrote portions<lb/> until
                    <date>December 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1886</date> when he was<lb/> no longer
                able. Having retired on<lb/> the night of <date>December 16<hi rend="sup"
                    >th</hi></date> he was<lb/> unable to rise the next morning and<lb/> never again
                left his bed. He died<lb/> surrounded by friends on <date>December<lb/> 30<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi> 1886</date> at 10.12 am.<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Mayer Sulzberger</persName><lb/>
                <date>May 9. 1887</date>. </p>
